qq,Richard Forsyth,ra_forsyth@yahoo.com,Re: Legitimate?,2018-12-13,I am a lawyer in the USA, by the way. I am not gunning after you guys or anything but I thought I'd throw you a couple of pieces of advice.

Another legitimacy issue you guys have is with your laser engraver. The images you're using are for a product that ran on Kickstarter and are only being sold by two approved entities, and they claim your use of their images and offer to sell their product is a scam. They specifically list Coolieshop. Now, I am willing to bet the product is actually made in China and maybe they're being sold on the side by the manufacturer or a partner of the manufacturer. But that would probably be a patent and/or copyright violation in ... well, the rest of the world and so it raises more legitimacy issues. This is a big reason so many people are reporting coolieshop to financial authorities, payment networks like MasterCard, and law enforcement.
Another thing is that your site uses a web template with a countdown theme that is used on other hastily setup shops that borrow media images. This does not exactly create confidence in the markets.

If you guys ARE legit, I wish you luck and I hope my little advice helps. If not, I am sure the trouble has already started for you folks because the dogs have already been let loose. Good luck with all the chargeback requests too.
